♪ Scrub, scrub ♪

35:37.459 --> 35:41.001
Oh, so you finally managed
to drag your lazy...

35:45.203 --> 35:47.700
Have you done something
with your hair?

35:48.074 --> 35:49.207
Maybe.

35:49.207 --> 35:50.439
Maybe not.

35:53.442 --> 35:54.707
Where’d you get
them dungarees?

35:54.707 --> 35:57.985
-  Lost property.

35:58.150 --> 35:59.547
Why,

35:59.987 --> 36:00.581
do they suit me?

36:00.581 --> 36:03.221
- Yeah.

36:03.221 --> 36:05.388
Not bad, I suppose.

36:06.389 --> 36:08.193
What’re you doing
all the way over there?

36:08.193 --> 36:10.459
- Keeping my knees warm.

36:10.459 --> 36:12.230
Well, why don’t you
come over here

36:12.230 --> 36:14.133
and have a glass o’ gin?

36:14.133 --> 36:16.399
Why don’t you come over here,

36:16.399 --> 36:18.137
where it’s all hot?

36:18.137 --> 36:20.601
Whoa!

36:20.601 --> 36:23.736
Oh! Oh, my Lord.

36:24.979 --> 36:26.607
Ladies and gentlemen,
may I present to you

36:26.607 --> 36:28.279
a brand-new contraption
of my creation,

36:28.279 --> 36:30.644
an innovation
in laundrification.

36:30.644 --> 36:31.678
♪ Scrub, scrub ♪

36:31.678 --> 36:34.252
Let me ask you a question,
how does Tiddles
wanna spend all his time?

36:34.252 --> 36:35.583
Chasing after mailmen.

36:35.583 --> 36:38.553
And what do I have
to do all day,
fellow scrubbers, please?

36:38.553 --> 36:39.488
♪ Scrub, scrub ♪

36:39.488 --> 36:42.392
But now, with Willy Wonka’s
Wild and Wonderful
Wishy-washy Wonka Walker,

36:42.392 --> 36:43.657
please don’t make me
say that again,

36:43.657 --> 36:46.066
Tiddles gets to run
and I can have fun.

36:46.066 --> 36:47.166
♪ Scrub, scrub ♪

36:47.166 --> 36:49.036
Just popping out for a bit.

36:49.036 --> 36:51.137
I’ll be back before roll call.

36:51.137 --> 36:53.172
Until then,
Tiddles has agreed to...

36:53.172 --> 36:56.241
- ♪ Scrub, scrub ♪

36:56.241 --> 36:59.343
So, tell me all about Bavaria.

36:59.343 --> 37:01.015
- Where?
- Where you’re from.

37:01.015 --> 37:03.281
Oh, yes. It’s very...

37:03.281 --> 37:06.251
- ...Bavarian.
-  Oh, whoo.

37:11.652 --> 37:13.126
All clear.

37:13.126 --> 37:14.424
Really?
- Yeah.

37:14.424 --> 37:16.558
We did it! Well done, Noodle.

37:16.558 --> 37:17.592
I can’t believe it worked.

37:17.592 --> 37:19.726
Wait till you see how much
chocolate I made last night.

37:19.726 --> 37:23.037
We sell this,
and we’re gonna be...

37:23.631 --> 37:24.797
Oh, no.

37:24.797 --> 37:26.469
What’s going on, Willy?

37:26.469 --> 37:27.305
Not again.

37:27.305 --> 37:28.339
Where are the chocolates?

37:28.339 --> 37:31.441
I don’t know how to tell you
this, Noodle, but...

37:31.441 --> 37:32.805
they’ve been stolen.

37:32.805 --> 37:34.543
- Stolen?
- Mm-hmm.

37:34.543 --> 37:35.610
Who by?

37:35.610 --> 37:38.415
The Little Orange Man.

37:38.415 --> 37:39.119
What?

37:39.119 --> 37:41.550
The Little Orange Man.
I didn’t tell you about him?

37:41.550 --> 37:43.090
No, ya didn’t.

37:43.090 --> 37:45.191
He’s my nemesis.
About yea high.

37:45.191 --> 37:46.456
Comes in the dead
of the night,

37:46.456 --> 37:47.721
and he steals
all my chocolate.

37:47.721 --> 37:51.692
Been happening every few weeks
for the past three,
four years now.

37:51.692 --> 37:52.495
Really?

37:52.495 --> 37:53.430
Sometimes I spy him

37:53.430 --> 37:55.630
in that strange realm
’twixt sleep and wake,

37:55.630 --> 37:57.830
green hair glinting
in the moonlight.

37:57.830 --> 37:58.732
Green hair?

37:58.732 --> 38:00.470
One day I shall
catch him, Noodle.

38:00.470 --> 38:01.669
- Willy.
- When I do...

38:01.669 --> 38:02.571
Willy!
- Hmm?

38:02.571 --> 38:04.738
You don’t seriously expect me
to believe this, do you?

38:04.738 --> 38:07.807
Of course I do. What other
explanation is there?

38:07.807 --> 38:08.643
I don’t know,

38:08.643 --> 38:10.216
that you go to sleep...
- Mm-hmm.

38:10.216 --> 38:11.547
...dream ’bout
Little Green Man...

38:11.547 --> 38:12.680
Orange man, green hair. Yeah.

38:12.680 --> 38:14.088
...and while you’re dreaming,

38:14.088 --> 38:16.222
stuff your face
with chocolate!

38:16.222 --> 38:18.125
Stuff my...

38:18.191 --> 38:19.258
That makes a lot more sense.

38:19.258 --> 38:20.490
Why’d I ever think
this would work?

38:20.490 --> 38:22.129
I’ve been eating
all my own chocolate?

38:22.129 --> 38:23.658
- Stupid Silver Linings.
- I don’t think I have been.

38:23.658 --> 38:24.329
Hey!

38:24.329 --> 38:25.759
There’s nothing stupid
about my chocolate.

38:25.759 --> 38:28.267
If Mrs. Scrubitt
had spotted us,

38:28.267 --> 38:30.137
I’d be in the coop right now.

38:30.137 --> 38:31.303
Look, I’m sorry, okay?

38:31.303 --> 38:32.865
But we can make
more chocolate.

38:32.865 --> 38:35.505
Only problem is
I’m all out of milk.

38:35.505 --> 38:38.343
Well, that’s not a problem.

38:38.409 --> 38:40.378
Milk.

38:40.378 --> 38:42.677
A, that is stealing.

38:42.677 --> 38:43.381
And C,

38:43.381 --> 38:45.713
Willy Wonka does not use
any old cow’s milk.

38:45.713 --> 38:46.813
For this particular creation,

38:46.813 --> 38:49.717
I require the milk
of a giraffe.

38:49.717 --> 38:50.784
Okay... fine.

38:50.784 --> 38:53.490
As a matter of fact,
there’s one at the zoo.

38:53.490 --> 38:54.260
Bingala!

38:54.260 --> 38:56.856
But A,
the zoo is not that way.

38:56.856 --> 38:58.132
Great.

38:58.132 --> 38:58.627
And B,

38:58.627 --> 39:01.564
they’re not gonna let you just
walk in there and milk it.

39:01.564 --> 39:05.436
Mm. That, my dear Noodle,
is why we’re very lucky

39:05.436 --> 39:09.407
the Little Orange Man
didn’t find this.

39:13.477 --> 39:14.280
What is it?

39:14.280 --> 39:15.380
From Zoo Management.

39:15.380 --> 39:18.746
In recognition
of your years of service.

39:18.746 --> 39:21.518
But I’ve only
been here a year.

39:21.584 --> 39:26.193
Which is why
there’s only one chocolate.

39:26.556 --> 39:27.491
Huh.

39:27.491 --> 39:28.690
Well, thank you very much.

39:28.690 --> 39:31.660
You’re welcome.
Good night!

39:32.298 --> 39:33.761
Hey, well done, Noodle.

39:33.761 --> 39:35.730
So, what is it really?

39:35.730 --> 39:37.204
It’s called A Big Night Out.

39:37.204 --> 39:38.667
A single chocolate
that perfectly mimics

39:38.667 --> 39:40.537
a night on the town.
-  Mmm.

39:40.537 --> 39:43.408
The outer layer,
a champagne truffle.

39:43.408 --> 39:44.409
That’s lovely.

39:44.409 --> 39:46.279
The next is white wine.

39:46.279 --> 39:47.346
Mmm.

39:47.346 --> 39:48.347
Followed by red.

39:48.347 --> 39:49.546
Now we are talking!

39:49.546 --> 39:51.284
That’s when the singing
and dancing starts.

39:51.284 --> 39:53.715
♪ We’re gonna
Have a party tonight!♪

39:53.715 --> 39:57.191
It’s when he hits
the layer o’ whiskey fudge
he’ll get emotional.

39:57.191 --> 39:59.952
She was
the only woman I ever loved!

39:59.952 --> 40:02.394
He might do
something reckless.

40:02.394 --> 40:03.527
I’ll give her a call.

40:03.527 --> 40:06.332
What harm could it do?

40:06.332 --> 40:07.861
Hello, Gwennie? It’s Basil.

40:07.861 --> 40:10.765
I just wanted to say,
I’ve always loved you.

40:10.765 --> 40:13.306
I love you so much. What?

40:13.306 --> 40:14.208
It’s Basil Bond.

40:14.208 --> 40:15.869
We sat together
in chemistry at school.

40:15.869 --> 40:16.936
No, no, don’t hang up!

40:16.936 --> 40:20.643
Finally, some old port
from the back
of the cupboard, and...

40:23.415 --> 40:24.350
Hmm.

40:24.350 --> 40:26.451
Let’s go.

40:26.451 --> 40:28.387
Noodle, let’s go.

40:29.553 --> 40:30.818
Why don’t they
fly away?

40:30.818 --> 40:34.294
I don’t know.
Perhaps they haven’t
thought of it.

40:34.294 --> 40:36.593
You’re kidding?
No, I’m serious.

40:36.593 --> 40:37.924
That’s the thing
about flamingos.

40:37.924 --> 40:40.597
They need someone
to show ’em the way.

40:40.597 --> 40:42.368
Huh.

40:45.602 --> 40:47.604
Giraffe.

40:47.736 --> 40:51.641
Giraffe. Giraffe.

40:52.609 --> 40:54.677
Ah! Giraffe.

40:59.583 --> 41:02.256
You have got to learn
how to read.

41:02.256 --> 41:02.817
Why?

41:02.817 --> 41:04.390
You were nearly
eaten by a tiger.

41:04.390 --> 41:05.721
"Nearly" is the key word
there, Noodle.

41:05.721 --> 41:07.525
I’ve nearly been eaten
by a lot of things,

41:07.525 --> 41:10.396
and none of them
got more than a nibble.

41:11.859 --> 41:12.860
Giraffe.

41:12.860 --> 41:15.335
Okay, I’ll learn how to read.

41:33.947 --> 41:37.951
Good evening,
Miss, um...

41:37.951 --> 41:40.327
Abigail.
-  Abigail.

41:40.954 --> 41:42.725
Whoa! Easy, now.

41:42.725 --> 41:44.892
I brought acacia mints.

41:51.030 --> 41:51.800
Oh.

41:51.800 --> 41:54.836
Giraffes are just crazy
about my acacia mints.

41:54.836 --> 41:56.475
Love ’em more
than anything else.

41:56.475 --> 41:59.709
Except being scratched
under the chin, you see?

42:01.315 --> 42:03.383
You wanna
give it a go, Noodle?

42:03.383 --> 42:04.648
Me?

42:04.648 --> 42:06.848
Yeah. Why not?

42:07.750 --> 42:09.653
Okay.

42:14.020 --> 42:15.054
- Ugh!
-  Oh!

42:15.054 --> 42:18.497
Think she likes you.

42:19.091 --> 42:20.433
Miss Abigail,

42:20.433 --> 42:22.897
if my colleague here
gives you a good scratch,

42:22.897 --> 42:24.899
do you think you could
possibly spare us

42:24.899 --> 42:27.341
a pint or two of your milk?

42:30.905 --> 42:33.743
So, have you done
this before?

42:33.743 --> 42:36.680
Once. In Africa.

42:36.680 --> 42:38.451
Magnificent beast.

42:38.451 --> 42:41.014
Was she wild?
Wild?

42:41.014 --> 42:43.489
She was absolutely furious.

42:43.489 --> 42:45.051
You sure can be silly, Willy.

42:45.051 --> 42:48.087
I suppose that’s true-dle,
Noodle.

42:48.087 --> 42:49.528
True-dle?

42:49.528 --> 42:51.024
That doesn’t work, does it?

42:51.024 --> 42:52.564
Nothing rhymes with Noodle.

42:52.564 --> 42:55.600
Where’d you get that name, anyway?

42:55.600 --> 42:57.096
Doesn’t matter.

42:57.503 --> 42:58.999
No, go on.

43:01.375 --> 43:02.871
This.

43:03.377 --> 43:06.138
It’s all I have
of my real parents. See?

43:06.138 --> 43:10.945
"N" for Noodle.
Or Nora, or Nina,

43:11.143 --> 43:13.013
or nothing at all.

43:13.013 --> 43:14.553
Can’t you trace the owner?

43:14.553 --> 43:16.819
You don’t think I’ve tried?

43:17.116 --> 43:18.656
When I was a kid,

43:18.656 --> 43:21.428
I always hoped
that I’d find my parents.

43:21.428 --> 43:25.465
And they’d live
in this beautiful old building
full of books.

43:25.465 --> 43:29.964
My mom, she’d be waiting there
for me at the door,

43:29.964 --> 43:30.998
and I’d run into her arms.

43:30.998 --> 43:35.706
She’d give me this big hug
like she’d never let me go.

43:36.740 --> 43:40.645
But then I realized
it was just a stupid dream.

43:42.042 --> 43:44.682
There’s nothing stupid
about that.

43:44.682 --> 43:45.650
Isn’t there?

43:45.650 --> 43:48.719
I know things haven’t
been easy for you, Noodle.

43:48.719 --> 43:49.819
But they’re gonna get better.

43:49.819 --> 43:53.823
I’m not gonna let you rot
in that Wash House forever.

43:53.823 --> 43:54.824
You promise?

43:54.824 --> 43:57.563
I can do better than that.

43:58.025 --> 43:58.993
I pinkie promise.

43:58.993 --> 44:01.996
And that’s the most
solemn vow there is.

44:04.966 --> 44:05.802
Get scratchin’.

44:05.802 --> 44:10.004
We don’t have long
until that guard comes
to-dle, Noodle.

44:10.004 --> 44:13.777
- To-dle!
- It’s not even a word!

44:13.843 --> 44:14.580
Oh.

44:14.580 --> 44:16.747
I’m gonna keep working on it.

44:18.617 --> 44:21.147
- ♪ For a moment ♪

44:21.147 --> 44:27.087
♪ Life doesn’t seem quite
So bad ♪

44:28.495 --> 44:31.190
♪ For a moment ♪

44:31.190 --> 44:36.800
♪ I kinda forgot to be sad ♪

44:37.834 --> 44:42.773
♪ He turns night to day ♪

44:42.905 --> 44:47.712
♪ But don’t get carried away ♪

44:47.712 --> 44:49.681
♪ Never let down your guard ♪

44:49.681 --> 44:55.181
♪ Let them into your heart
For a moment ♪

44:56.655 --> 44:59.020
♪ Not for a moment ♪

44:59.020 --> 45:02.056
I got it, Noodle!
Listen to this.

45:02.056 --> 45:07.501
♪ Noodle, Noodle,
Apple strudel ♪

45:07.501 --> 45:09.129
♪ Some people don’t ♪

45:09.129 --> 45:11.065
♪ And some people doodle ♪

45:11.065 --> 45:16.103
♪ Snakes, flamingos,
Bears, and poodles ♪

