a good look at you.

01:00:15.705 --> 01:00:17.410
-  Wow.

01:00:17.410 --> 01:00:18.037
Good evening.

01:00:18.037 --> 01:00:20.710
So you’re the funny little man
who’s been following me.

01:00:20.710 --> 01:00:23.515
"Funny little man"?
How dare you.

01:00:23.515 --> 01:00:24.450
I will have you know

01:00:24.450 --> 01:00:26.177
that I am a perfectly
respectable size

01:00:26.177 --> 01:00:28.586
for an Oompa Loompa.

01:00:28.586 --> 01:00:29.521
An Oompa-what-now?

01:00:29.521 --> 01:00:32.788
In fact, in Loompaland,
I am regarded
as something of a whopper.

01:00:32.788 --> 01:00:34.460
They call me Lofty.

01:00:34.460 --> 01:00:36.627
So, I will thank you
to stop gawping at me

01:00:36.627 --> 01:00:37.892
as though I was
something unpleasant

01:00:37.892 --> 01:00:39.190
you’d found
in your handkerchief.

01:00:39.190 --> 01:00:43.436
I find it uncomfortable
and, frankly, rude.

01:00:43.436 --> 01:00:44.503
Um...

01:00:44.503 --> 01:00:45.933
- Sorry.
- Now let me out of here.

01:00:45.933 --> 01:00:47.440
You have absolutely no right

01:00:47.440 --> 01:00:50.542
to go around
embottling innocent strangers.

01:00:50.542 --> 01:00:51.103
Innocent?

01:00:51.103 --> 01:00:53.974
Hold on, you’ve been
stealing from me. For years.

01:00:53.974 --> 01:00:55.976
Well, you started it.

01:00:55.976 --> 01:00:56.680
Me?

01:00:56.680 --> 01:00:58.946
You stole our cocoa beans.

01:00:58.946 --> 01:01:01.113
What are you talking about?

01:01:01.113 --> 01:01:04.886
Do you mean
that you don’t even remember?

01:01:04.886 --> 01:01:06.525
Remember what?

01:01:06.525 --> 01:01:09.121
The day you...

01:01:09.187 --> 01:01:11.189
destroyed my life.

01:01:11.189 --> 01:01:13.697
No, I don’t remember that.

01:01:13.697 --> 01:01:14.731
Well then, young man.

01:01:14.731 --> 01:01:16.161
Allow me
to refresh your memory

01:01:16.161 --> 01:01:19.571
in the form of a song
so ruinously catchy

01:01:19.571 --> 01:01:21.969
that it may never
leave your mind.

01:01:22.904 --> 01:01:24.169
Oh, I don’t think
I wanna hear that.

01:01:24.169 --> 01:01:25.709
- Too late.

01:01:25.709 --> 01:01:26.776
I’ve started dancing now.

01:01:26.776 --> 01:01:29.878
Once we’ve started,
we can’t stop, you see.

01:01:31.011 --> 01:01:33.948
♪ Oompa Loompa doompety-doo ♪

01:01:33.948 --> 01:01:37.721
♪ I’ve got a tragic tale
For you ♪

01:01:37.721 --> 01:01:40.658
♪ Oompa Loompa doompety-dee ♪

01:01:40.658 --> 01:01:43.023
♪ If you are wise,
You’ll listen to me ♪

01:01:43.023 --> 01:01:47.192
- ♪ Dear Loompaland
Is both luscious and green ♪

01:01:47.192 --> 01:01:50.734
♪ But not conducive
To growing the bean ♪

01:01:50.734 --> 01:01:54.837
♪ My job was guarding
What little we’d got ♪

01:01:54.837 --> 01:01:56.036
♪ You came along ♪

01:01:56.036 --> 01:01:57.906
♪ And pinched the lot ♪

01:01:57.906 --> 01:01:59.677
Hey, why didn’t you
say something?

01:01:59.677 --> 01:02:01.107
Well, perhaps I drifted off.

01:02:01.107 --> 01:02:04.616
- ♪ Oompa Loompa doompety-day ♪

01:02:04.616 --> 01:02:07.850
♪ When I awoke,
They sent me away ♪

01:02:07.850 --> 01:02:10.655
♪ I’m disgraced,
Cast out in the cold ♪

01:02:10.655 --> 01:02:15.528
♪ Till I’ve paid my friends
Back a thousandfold ♪

01:02:15.528 --> 01:02:18.630
A thousandfold?
You gotta be kidding me!

01:02:18.630 --> 01:02:20.027
I repeat...

01:02:20.027 --> 01:02:23.701
♪ A thousandfold ♪

01:02:24.295 --> 01:02:25.263
Hah. Wow.

01:02:25.263 --> 01:02:27.199
Um...
Mr. Loompa,

01:02:27.199 --> 01:02:29.707
if you really think
that’s a reasonable penalty

01:02:29.707 --> 01:02:31.302
for taking three beans...

01:02:31.302 --> 01:02:32.677
Four beans.

01:02:32.677 --> 01:02:33.304
...four beans,

01:02:33.304 --> 01:02:35.174
then I’m sure we can come
to some sort of understanding.

01:02:35.174 --> 01:02:37.880
But I can’t give you
my entire supply.

01:02:37.880 --> 01:02:40.080
I got people counting on me.

01:02:40.080 --> 01:02:42.148
Hmm.

01:02:42.148 --> 01:02:43.556
Very well.

01:02:43.556 --> 01:02:44.755
I tell you what.

01:02:44.755 --> 01:02:45.690
You let me out of here,

01:02:45.690 --> 01:02:49.727
and we can discuss it,
like gentlemen. Hmm?

01:02:50.156 --> 01:02:51.861
All right.

01:02:52.059 --> 01:02:55.128
Ah, thank you.
Now, would you be so very kind

01:02:55.128 --> 01:02:58.703
as to pass me
that miniature frying pan?

01:02:58.703 --> 01:02:59.671
Hmm. This one?

01:02:59.671 --> 01:03:02.201
No, no.
The heavier one, please.

01:03:02.201 --> 01:03:03.741
All right.

01:03:03.741 --> 01:03:04.808
Thank you. Thank you very...

01:03:04.808 --> 01:03:07.074
Ooh, I say, that is quite
a beast, isn’t it?

01:03:07.074 --> 01:03:08.614
Now, come a little closer.

01:03:08.614 --> 01:03:09.846
That’s it, closer,
closer, closer,

01:03:09.846 --> 01:03:11.243
come on, cozy on up.
-  Okay.

01:03:11.243 --> 01:03:13.212
- There we are.
-  What?

01:03:13.212 --> 01:03:15.115
- Ow!

01:03:17.656 --> 01:03:18.250
Ow!

01:03:18.250 --> 01:03:20.659
Oompa Loompas
do not negotiate.

01:03:20.659 --> 01:03:21.759
Good day, sir.

01:03:21.759 --> 01:03:23.629
But that’s my last jar!

01:03:23.629 --> 01:03:26.225
I said good day.

01:03:27.633 --> 01:03:29.096
-  He came back?

01:03:29.096 --> 01:03:31.802
Yes, Noodle,
but this time I set a trap.

01:03:31.802 --> 01:03:34.068
And he walked right into it.

01:03:34.134 --> 01:03:34.937
So, where is he?

01:03:34.937 --> 01:03:37.071
Ah, well, we had
a fight, you see. He won.

01:03:37.071 --> 01:03:38.743
Hit me on the head
with a frying pan

01:03:38.743 --> 01:03:40.140
and jumped out of the window.

01:03:40.140 --> 01:03:43.077
Of course he did.

01:03:43.143 --> 01:03:45.112
You don’t believe me, do you?

01:03:45.112 --> 01:03:46.751
Honestly? No.

01:03:46.751 --> 01:03:47.851
No!

01:03:47.851 --> 01:03:48.379
No.

01:03:48.379 --> 01:03:50.722
- No.
- Definitely not.

01:03:50.722 --> 01:03:51.349
But,

01:03:51.349 --> 01:03:52.823
as it so happens,

01:03:52.823 --> 01:03:55.056
we don’t need
to sell chocolate today.

01:03:55.056 --> 01:03:55.958
And why is that?

01:03:55.958 --> 01:03:57.025
You know that shop?

01:03:57.025 --> 01:03:59.764
The one you’ve
been dreaming of?

01:04:13.910 --> 01:04:16.748
Now, I know
what you’re thinking.

01:04:16.748 --> 01:04:19.916
It may need a little work.

01:04:20.851 --> 01:04:22.380
Looks like someone
left the water running

01:04:22.380 --> 01:04:24.184
twenty years ago
and the ceiling fell through.

01:04:24.184 --> 01:04:27.154
And the ceiling above that,
and the ceiling above that.

01:04:27.154 --> 01:04:29.926
But that means
we can afford it.

01:04:29.926 --> 01:04:31.026
For a week, anyway.

01:04:31.026 --> 01:04:32.929
And we’d finally
be legitimate.

01:04:32.929 --> 01:04:34.898
The police wouldn’t
have any excuse

01:04:34.898 --> 01:04:36.768
to keep bothering us.

01:04:36.768 --> 01:04:39.969
So,
what do you think, Willy?

01:04:39.969 --> 01:04:41.707
Do you like it?

01:04:43.269 --> 01:04:45.271
Do I like it?

01:04:47.042 --> 01:04:48.945
Noodle, it’s just
as I always imagined.

01:04:48.945 --> 01:04:52.817
No, scratch that,
it’s better than I imagined.

01:04:52.817 --> 01:04:53.884
I mean, look at this place.

01:04:53.884 --> 01:04:56.381
I mean, yeah, it’s a wreck,
but... the potential!

01:04:56.381 --> 01:04:57.690
The bones!

01:04:57.690 --> 01:05:00.187
You mark my words,
this is gonna
be the best chocolate shop

01:05:00.187 --> 01:05:01.826
the world has ever seen.
- Whoo!

01:05:01.826 --> 01:05:03.762
You won’t be scrub-scrubbin’
much longer, Noodle.

01:05:03.762 --> 01:05:05.863
-  We’ll all be free.

01:05:05.863 --> 01:05:07.700
As free as flamingos!

01:05:19.173 --> 01:05:21.241
There’s six of them
in total.

01:05:21.241 --> 01:05:22.275
Including the little girl.

01:05:22.275 --> 01:05:24.310
She seems to be the brains
of the operation.

01:05:24.310 --> 01:05:28.149
They’re based out of a laundry
called Scrubitt and Bleacher.

01:05:28.149 --> 01:05:30.250
Scrubitt’s?

01:05:30.250 --> 01:05:32.318
That’s right. Why, you know it?

01:05:32.318 --> 01:05:34.892
Yes, as a matter of fact,
I do.

01:05:34.892 --> 01:05:36.091
They just
rented a shop.

01:05:36.091 --> 01:05:38.390
So, legally, I can’t
touch them. But illegally,

01:05:38.390 --> 01:05:40.964
I’m happy to do
whatever you guys want.

01:05:40.964 --> 01:05:43.032
You want ’em all
to have a little accident?

01:05:43.032 --> 01:05:44.363
In which they die?

01:05:44.363 --> 01:05:45.232
Not a problem.

01:05:45.232 --> 01:05:47.399
But it’s gonna cost you
a lot more chocolate.

01:05:47.399 --> 01:05:48.367
It’s all right, Chief.

01:05:48.367 --> 01:05:50.501
And also, I’d, uh,
be grateful for an advance.

01:05:50.501 --> 01:05:53.746
’Cause the last boxes
you gave me...

01:05:53.746 --> 01:05:55.143
they’re gone.

01:05:55.143 --> 01:05:55.946
All of them?

01:05:55.946 --> 01:05:57.277
I’ve been eating
these little paper cases

01:05:57.277 --> 01:05:58.850
for the... for the past
three days.

01:05:58.850 --> 01:06:01.314
You know, you think they’re
gonna give you the same hit.

01:06:01.314 --> 01:06:03.481
They don’t.

01:06:03.481 --> 01:06:04.416
Oh.

01:06:04.416 --> 01:06:05.890
There you go, Chief.

01:06:05.890 --> 01:06:08.189
There’s plenty more
where that came from.

01:06:08.189 --> 01:06:09.927
You stand down for now.

01:06:09.927 --> 01:06:12.127
We’ll give you a call
when the time is right.

01:06:18.331 --> 01:06:19.464
What is it, Arthur?

01:06:19.464 --> 01:06:20.432
The girl.

01:06:20.432 --> 01:06:23.941
You don’t really think
it could be her, do you?

01:06:24.403 --> 01:06:25.107
I do.

01:06:25.107 --> 01:06:28.407
You always assured us
she wouldn’t be a problem.

01:06:28.407 --> 01:06:30.816
He’s right. You did assure us.

01:06:30.816 --> 01:06:32.411
And she won’t be.

01:06:32.411 --> 01:06:33.544
Nor will Wonka.

01:06:33.544 --> 01:06:36.547
I’ll see to it, personally.

01:06:39.088 --> 01:06:41.552
Who is it?
What d’you want?

01:06:44.159 --> 01:06:46.557
Mr. Slugworth.

01:06:46.557 --> 01:06:48.801
Just a minute, sir.

01:06:49.362 --> 01:06:50.198
Good evening.

01:06:50.198 --> 01:06:53.465
- Good evening.
-  Who is it,
puffy-wu...

01:06:53.465 --> 01:06:55.302
-  Stone me.

01:06:55.302 --> 01:06:56.237
It’s Mr. Slugworth.

01:06:56.237 --> 01:06:58.877
To what do we owe the honor?

01:06:58.877 --> 01:07:01.308
You have a guest.
A Mr. Wonka?

01:07:01.308 --> 01:07:03.211
He’s been sneaking out
to sell chocolate

01:07:03.211 --> 01:07:05.180
with the help
of your serving girl.

01:07:05.180 --> 01:07:07.050
Why, that little brat.

01:07:07.050 --> 01:07:08.018
Well, quite.

01:07:08.018 --> 01:07:12.286
I wondered if you might
help me put an end to their...

01:07:12.352 --> 01:07:14.123
business.

01:07:22.901 --> 01:07:25.233
Here we go, Mamma.

01:07:33.439 --> 01:07:37.377
Ladies and gentlemen,
greetings to you all,

01:07:37.377 --> 01:07:40.314
and welcome to Wonka’s.

01:07:40.314 --> 01:07:42.349
Tremendous things
are in store,

01:07:42.349 --> 01:07:46.254
both literally
and metaphorically.

01:07:46.254 --> 01:07:47.585
What?

01:07:47.585 --> 01:07:49.356
In there?

01:07:49.994 --> 01:07:51.424
Humor me.

01:07:51.490 --> 01:07:56.594
♪ Close your eyes
And count to ten ♪

01:07:58.101 --> 01:08:00.169
♪ Make a wish ♪

01:08:00.169 --> 01:08:02.138
♪ Now ♪

01:08:02.138 --> 01:08:04.371
♪ Open them ♪

01:08:05.240 --> 01:08:09.607
♪ Here’s a store
That’s like no other ♪

01:08:09.607 --> 01:08:13.952
♪ If it were,
I wouldn’t bother ♪

01:08:13.952 --> 01:08:17.450
- ♪ Chocolate bushes ♪

01:08:17.450 --> 01:08:19.023
♪ Chocolate trees ♪

01:08:19.023 --> 01:08:22.895
♪ Chocolate flowers
And chocolate bees ♪

01:08:22.895 --> 01:08:26.965
- ♪ Chocolate memories ♪

01:08:26.965 --> 01:08:30.969
♪ That a boy once saved ♪

01:08:32.597 --> 01:08:35.908
♪ Before they melted away ♪

01:08:35.908 --> 01:08:40.407
♪ A world of your own ♪

01:08:40.407 --> 01:08:44.312
♪ A place to escape to ♪

01:08:44.950 --> 01:08:48.646
♪ A world of your own ♪

01:08:49.284 --> 01:08:52.287
♪ Where you can be free ♪

01:08:53.926 --> 01:08:57.457
♪ Wherever you go ♪

01:08:58.194 --> 01:09:02.693
♪ Wherever life takes you ♪

01:09:02.693 --> 01:09:06.565
♪ This is your home ♪

01:09:07.038 --> 01:09:10.041
♪ A world of your own ♪

01:09:17.378 --> 01:09:19.083
♪ Here is the child ♪

01:09:19.083 --> 01:09:21.679
♪ That you left behind ♪

01:09:21.679 --> 01:09:23.483
♪ Here is the kid ♪

01:09:23.483 --> 01:09:25.617
♪ With the curious mind ♪

01:09:25.617 --> 01:09:30.259
♪ Here is the wonder
We used to feel ♪

01:09:30.259 --> 01:09:33.394
♪ Back when the magic
Was real ♪

01:09:33.394 --> 01:09:38.003
♪ A world of your own ♪

01:09:38.003 --> 01:09:42.403
♪ A place to go when you’re ♪

01:09:43.140 --> 01:09:46.209
♪ Feeling alone ♪

01:09:47.540 --> 01:09:51.082
♪ Feeling unsure ♪

01:09:51.082 --> 01:09:51.544
Mmm!

01:09:51.544 --> 01:09:56.087
♪ Embrace the unknown ♪

01:09:56.087 --> 01:10:00.993
♪ Enjoy the adventure ♪

01:10:01.653 --> 01:10:06.658
♪ Let’s go strolling
In the clouds ♪

01:10:06.658 --> 01:10:09.100
♪ Grab a handful ♪

01:10:09.100 --> 01:10:10.530
♪ It’s allowed ♪

01:10:10.530 --> 01:10:15.139
♪ Clouds are made
Of cotton candy ♪

01:10:15.139 --> 01:10:19.209
♪ Just keep
Your umbrella handy ♪

01:10:19.209 --> 01:10:24.181
♪ ’Cause there’s
A hard rain gonna fall ♪

01:10:24.544 --> 01:10:26.084
♪ Humbugs, gumdrops ♪

01:10:26.084 --> 01:10:27.712
♪ And aniseed balls ♪

01:10:27.712 --> 01:10:31.023
- ♪ Fireworks bring ♪

01:10:31.023 --> 01:10:36.193
♪ Sugar string to chew ♪

01:10:37.128 --> 01:10:42.265
♪ All the colors
Of the rainbow ♪

01:10:42.265 --> 01:10:44.564
♪ And some others, too ♪

01:10:44.564 --> 01:10:47.072
♪ A world of our own ♪

01:10:47.072 --> 01:10:48.502
♪ A world of our own ♪

01:10:48.502 --> 01:10:53.045
- ♪ A place to escape to ♪
- ♪ A place to escape to ♪

01:10:53.045 --> 01:10:58.413
- ♪ A world of our own ♪
- ♪ A world of our own ♪

01:10:58.413 --> 01:11:00.052
♪ Where we can be free ♪

01:11:00.052 --> 01:11:02.714
♪ That’s where we can be free ♪

01:11:02.714 --> 01:11:07.191
♪ Wherever you go ♪

01:11:07.191 --> 01:11:12.163
♪ Wherever life takes you ♪

01:11:12.163 --> 01:11:16.101
♪ This is our home ♪

01:11:16.101 --> 01:11:20.204
♪ A world of our own ♪

01:11:24.307 --> 01:11:27.277
So, mushrooms,
pears, assorted flowers.

01:11:27.277 --> 01:11:30.346
That comes to 89 sovereigns.

01:11:30.346 --> 01:11:32.843
A bargain at twice the price.

01:11:32.843 --> 01:11:33.646
Thank you, sir.

01:11:33.646 --> 01:11:36.253
And how would
you like your change?

01:11:36.253 --> 01:11:38.321
Spendable or edible?

01:11:38.321 --> 01:11:40.653
Oh, edible, please.

01:11:41.522 --> 01:11:42.820
Enjoy.

01:11:42.820 --> 01:11:46.230
And, uh, don’t forget
to eat your basket.

01:11:46.230 --> 01:11:47.264
Oh.

01:11:47.264 --> 01:11:50.168
Abacus, that man just
gave us 100 sovereigns.

01:11:50.168 --> 01:11:52.764
I know, Noodle!

01:11:52.764 --> 01:11:53.666
Who’s next?

01:11:53.666 --> 01:11:55.173
That’ll be me.
Me!

01:11:59.771 --> 01:12:00.772
Uh...

01:12:00.772 --> 01:12:02.147
Mr. Wonka?

01:12:02.147 --> 01:12:03.643
Yes?

01:12:03.874 --> 01:12:05.711
What’s going on here?

01:12:05.711 --> 01:12:07.185
Oh, my goodness.

01:12:07.185 --> 01:12:08.549
That’s impossible.

01:12:08.549 --> 01:12:10.386
Unless...

01:12:13.191 --> 01:12:15.424
Yeti sweat?

01:12:15.424 --> 01:12:17.591
The most powerful
hair potion in the world.

01:12:17.591 --> 01:12:19.494
But I didn’t put it in there.

01:12:19.494 --> 01:12:22.200
Ladies and gentlemen!
Your attention, please!

01:12:22.200 --> 01:12:24.631
There appears
to be a manufacturing error.

01:12:24.631 --> 01:12:26.567
Nobody eat the flowers!

01:12:26.567 --> 01:12:28.602
Uh, why not?

01:12:28.602 --> 01:12:29.537
What’s wrong with them?

01:12:29.537 --> 01:12:31.242
What’s the matter
with this toadstool?

01:12:31.242 --> 01:12:33.640
My daughter took one bite,
and just look at her!

01:12:33.640 --> 01:12:36.577
There’s nothing wrong
with the chocolate milk,

01:12:36.577 --> 01:12:37.347
is there?

01:12:37.347 --> 01:12:38.447
I’m terribly sorry, everyone,

01:12:38.447 --> 01:12:40.152
and I don’t know
how to explain this, but...

01:12:40.152 --> 01:12:42.682
it appears that the chocolates
have been poisoned!

01:12:42.682 --> 01:12:43.782
- Poisoned?

01:12:43.782 --> 01:12:45.652
- Poisoned?
- He poisoned my child!

01:12:45.652 --> 01:12:47.687
I didn’t...
I didn’t poison them.

01:12:47.687 --> 01:12:49.524
I want my money back.

01:12:49.524 --> 01:12:50.855
I want compensation.

01:12:50.855 --> 01:12:52.824
I want revenge.

01:12:53.660 --> 01:12:54.793
Whoa!

01:13:00.271 --> 01:13:01.800
No, no! Please!

01:13:05.771 --> 01:13:09.775
This is what you get for
mustach-ing my daughter!

01:13:11.381 --> 01:13:15.220
I’ll wait for you.
Help! I have
to get away from this place.

01:13:15.913 --> 01:13:17.717
And that, I believe,

01:13:17.717 --> 01:13:21.853
is the end
of Wonka’s Chocolate Shop.

01:13:40.476 --> 01:13:42.775
I don’t understand.
What...

01:13:44.678 --> 01:13:45.943
What...

01:13:46.581 --> 01:13:47.549
What happened?

01:13:47.549 --> 01:13:49.419
Isn’t it obvious?

01:13:49.419 --> 01:13:51.982
The Chocolate Cartel.

01:13:53.819 --> 01:13:56.888
It’s okay, Willy.
We can rebuild.

01:13:56.888 --> 01:13:58.263
We can start again.

01:13:58.263 --> 01:14:00.595
There’s no point, Noodle.

01:14:01.464 --> 01:14:03.334
It didn’t work.

01:14:03.334 --> 01:14:04.599
What do you mean?

01:14:04.599 --> 01:14:07.470
She promised
she would be here.

01:14:08.801 --> 01:14:09.967
She wasn’t.

01:14:09.967 --> 01:14:12.409
You didn’t actually
think that...

01:14:12.409 --> 01:14:13.938
No, I did.

01:14:16.281 --> 01:14:16.941
Stupid dream.

01:14:16.941 --> 01:14:19.548
Don’t say that, Willy.
Please don’t ever...

01:14:19.548 --> 01:14:21.286
Come on, Noodle.

01:14:21.286 --> 01:14:25.015
I think Mr. Wonka
needs to be alone.

01:14:35.300 --> 01:14:41.471
Every good thing
in this world
started with a dream.

01:14:43.968 --> 01:14:46.740
So you hold on to yours.

01:14:46.740 --> 01:14:52.317
And when
you do share chocolate
with the world, oh...

01:14:52.944 --> 01:14:56.585
I’ll be right there beside ya.

01:14:57.553 --> 01:15:01.293
Terrible shame,
what happened here.

01:15:02.426 --> 01:15:03.757
Take it you’re
responsible?

01:15:03.757 --> 01:15:06.826
Us? Oh, no.
Well, not personally.

01:15:06.826 --> 01:15:10.566
We may have
encouraged Mrs. Scrubitt

01:15:10.566 --> 01:15:12.370
to enhance your creations.

01:15:12.370 --> 01:15:13.668
We paid her
to poison them.

01:15:13.668 --> 01:15:17.375
Yes,
thank you, Gerald.
You’re welcome.

01:15:17.375 --> 01:15:19.003
So why have you come?

01:15:19.003 --> 01:15:20.906
- To gloat?
- Oh, no, Mr. Wonka,

01:15:20.906 --> 01:15:23.414
I don’t waste my time
with that sort of thing.

01:15:23.414 --> 01:15:26.417
We’ve come
to offer you a deal.

01:15:26.417 --> 01:15:32.082
This is the precise amount
you owe Mrs. Scrubitt.

01:15:32.082 --> 01:15:35.723
This is for
the number cruncher,

01:15:35.921 --> 01:15:37.395
the plumber,

01:15:37.395 --> 01:15:39.529
the telephonist,

01:15:39.529 --> 01:15:43.335
the so-called funny-man,

01:15:43.335 --> 01:15:45.535
and this...

01:15:46.635 --> 01:15:47.570
is for the girl.

01:15:47.570 --> 01:15:49.638
Now, we put in
a bit extra for her.

01:15:49.638 --> 01:15:51.937
So that she can
get a place to live,

01:15:51.937 --> 01:15:53.774
clothes, toys...

01:15:54.610 --> 01:15:56.480
books.

01:15:56.810 --> 01:15:58.713
Oh, yes, Mr. Wonka.

01:15:58.713 --> 01:16:04.521
You could change her life.
Change all their lives.

01:16:05.390 --> 01:16:07.524
And what would I have to do?

01:16:07.689 --> 01:16:09.460
Leave town.

01:16:09.625 --> 01:16:11.561
Oh, and, um,

01:16:11.693 --> 01:16:14.894
never make chocolate again.

01:16:14.894 --> 01:16:17.061
There’s a boat
sailing at midnight.

01:16:17.061 --> 01:16:19.668
And for their sake,
as much as your own,

01:16:19.668 --> 01:16:22.704
I hope you’re onboard.

01:16:26.070 --> 01:16:28.776
♪ Sorry, Noodle ♪

01:16:30.877 --> 01:16:36.014
♪ I guess I got carried away ♪

01:16:38.522 --> 01:16:40.986
♪ Sorry, Noodle ♪

01:16:42.526 --> 01:16:46.024
♪ I hope you’ll forgive me
One day ♪

01:16:46.024 --> 01:16:50.127
Checking out,
are we?
Yeah.

01:16:52.965 --> 01:16:56.936
♪ I just wanted it ♪

01:16:56.936 --> 01:17:02.007
♪ To feel the way that it did ♪

01:17:02.007 --> 01:17:05.549
♪ When I was a kid ♪

01:17:09.014 --> 01:17:11.819
♪ Sorry, Noodle ♪

01:17:16.989 --> 01:17:18.925
Ah, Mr. Wonka.

01:17:18.925 --> 01:17:21.928
Your ticket. Uh, one-way.

01:17:21.928 --> 01:17:23.666
To the North Pole.

01:17:23.666 --> 01:17:25.030
It’s premium economy.

01:17:25.030 --> 01:17:26.702
Yeah,
it’s basically economy.

01:17:26.702 --> 01:17:28.638
I mean, yeah,
you get a little more legroom.

01:17:28.638 --> 01:17:30.541
A complimentary
packet of peanuts.

01:17:30.541 --> 01:17:31.509
Is it worth the extra?

01:17:31.509 --> 01:17:34.941
I don’t know.
But these guys...

01:17:34.941 --> 01:17:37.746
We don’t need
to go into detail.

01:17:37.746 --> 01:17:39.044
Goodbye,

01:17:39.616 --> 01:17:41.211
Mr. Wonka.

01:17:58.162 --> 01:17:59.999
Thank you.

01:18:32.702 --> 01:18:36.068
♪ Oompa Loompa doompety-dee ♪

01:18:36.068 --> 01:18:39.038
♪ I’m not in premium economy ♪

01:18:39.038 --> 01:18:42.778
♪ I’d go first class
If I were you ♪

01:18:42.778 --> 01:18:45.781
♪ That’s what Oompa Loompas ♪

01:18:45.781 --> 01:18:47.112
♪ Doompety-do!♪

01:18:49.180 --> 01:18:50.115
So glad you’re here.

01:18:50.115 --> 01:18:53.085
Oh, I’m not going to let you
out of my sight, Willy Wonka.

01:18:53.085 --> 01:18:54.625
Not till you’ve
paid your debt.

01:18:54.625 --> 01:18:58.530
But I bring glad tidings
on that score.

01:18:58.530 --> 01:18:59.256
What’s that?

01:18:59.256 --> 01:19:01.027
I’ve been doing my sums.

01:19:01.027 --> 01:19:03.260
One more jar, and we’re even.

01:19:03.260 --> 01:19:06.703
Or, if you prefer,
I will accept half a jar

01:19:06.703 --> 01:19:08.705
of those rather
amusing Hoverchocs.

01:19:08.705 --> 01:19:10.806
- You’re outta luck.

01:19:10.806 --> 01:19:11.972
I don’t make chocolate
anymore.

01:19:11.972 --> 01:19:16.207
Oh, dear, please don’t tell me
you’re going to go through
with this ridiculous deal?

01:19:16.207 --> 01:19:17.241
I have to.

01:19:17.241 --> 01:19:19.045
For Noodle.

01:19:19.045 --> 01:19:21.817
I promised her a better life.

01:19:22.048 --> 01:19:22.950
I pinkie promised.

01:19:22.950 --> 01:19:24.886
You should stand up
to those bullies.

01:19:24.886 --> 01:19:26.019
Give ’em the old one-two.

01:19:26.019 --> 01:19:29.055
That’s what
an Oompa Loompa would do.

01:19:31.057 --> 01:19:32.091
But if you are determined

01:19:32.091 --> 01:19:35.160
to just sit there
feeling sorry for yourself,

01:19:35.160 --> 01:19:36.931
I am going flat.

01:19:36.931 --> 01:19:38.669
Good night, sir.

01:19:47.238 --> 01:19:48.338
Huh.

01:19:51.275 --> 01:19:54.179
What is it?

01:19:54.179 --> 01:19:54.982
No, nothing.

01:19:54.982 --> 01:19:58.689
Well, it’s obviously something
because you said, "Huh."

01:19:58.689 --> 01:20:01.021
I’m sorry. Forget it.

01:20:01.351 --> 01:20:05.025
- Very well.

01:20:09.062 --> 01:20:09.733
Huh.

01:20:09.733 --> 01:20:11.130
Oh, you did it again.

01:20:11.130 --> 01:20:12.736
Tell me what it is,
or I shall poke you

01:20:12.736 --> 01:20:14.034
quite viciously
with a cocktail stick.

01:20:14.034 --> 01:20:16.135
Look. Where Slugworth
shook my hand.

01:20:16.135 --> 01:20:17.972
His ring left a mark. See?

01:20:17.972 --> 01:20:19.875
It’s an "A,"
surrounded by "S"s.

01:20:19.875 --> 01:20:22.746
So what?
His name is Arthur Slugworth.

01:20:22.746 --> 01:20:24.110
It’s probably a family ring.

01:20:24.110 --> 01:20:26.277
Yes, but Noodle has one
just like it.

01:20:26.277 --> 01:20:27.146
- Noodle?
- Uh-huh.

01:20:27.146 --> 01:20:31.315
Why would Noodle the orphan
have a Slugworth family ring?

01:20:31.315 --> 01:20:33.889
There’s only one reason
I can think of.

01:20:33.889 --> 01:20:34.659
Which is?

01:20:34.659 --> 01:20:36.254
And if I’m correct, Noodle
could be in grave danger.

01:20:36.254 --> 01:20:38.630
Well, come on, Wonka.
Spit it out.

01:20:38.630 --> 01:20:40.258
Produce your owl pellet
of wisdom.

01:20:40.258 --> 01:20:42.260
There’s no time.
I gotta get back.

01:20:42.260 --> 01:20:43.734
Captain!
- Wonka?

01:20:43.734 --> 01:20:48.002
Come back here. Wonka!
I demand an explanation.

01:20:48.002 --> 01:20:49.333
Captain?

01:20:49.872 --> 01:20:54.404
On second thoughts,
the explanation can wait.

01:20:54.404 --> 01:20:56.175
Good day to you.

01:21:04.656 --> 01:21:05.382
Well, gentlemen,

01:21:05.382 --> 01:21:09.419
one dead chocolatier,
as requested.

01:21:10.695 --> 01:21:11.322
Miss Bon-Bon?

01:21:11.322 --> 01:21:13.126
Yes, Mr. Slugworth?

01:21:13.126 --> 01:21:15.667
Give the chief his chocolate.

01:21:23.268 --> 01:21:24.775
My, my.

01:21:24.775 --> 01:21:27.041
What a lot o’ long faces
this morning.

01:21:27.041 --> 01:21:30.308
It’s almost as though you lot
had a sneaky little scheme

01:21:30.308 --> 01:21:32.112
to try and wriggle out
of your contracts.

01:21:32.112 --> 01:21:35.753
Which spectacularly misfired.

01:21:35.753 --> 01:21:38.151
But I’ve got some good news
for you lot,

01:21:38.151 --> 01:21:39.185
not that you deserve it.

01:21:39.185 --> 01:21:43.695
Your friend, Mr. Wonka,
done a deal with Mr. Slugworth.

01:21:43.695 --> 01:21:44.190
What?

01:21:44.190 --> 01:21:48.799
Gave up on his dream
to settle your accounts.

01:21:48.865 --> 01:21:51.230
Mr. Crunch.
- Present.

01:21:54.398 --> 01:21:56.301
You’re free to go.

01:21:57.170 --> 01:21:58.006
Scram, bookworm.

01:21:58.006 --> 01:21:59.711
Bell.
Hello.

01:21:59.711 --> 01:22:01.306
Sling yer hook.

01:22:01.306 --> 01:22:02.010
Benz.

01:22:02.010 --> 01:22:04.111
You ain’t gotta tell me twice.

01:22:04.111 --> 01:22:05.277
Chucklesworth.

01:22:05.277 --> 01:22:07.378
You’ve been
a terrible audience.

01:22:07.378 --> 01:22:08.181
Good night!

01:22:08.181 --> 01:22:09.919
Yeah, well, you ain’t been
much of a comedian, mate.

01:22:09.919 --> 01:22:12.053
I know.
- Hey, Larry.

01:22:12.053 --> 01:22:15.287
Keep going.
You’ve got something.

01:22:15.287 --> 01:22:16.156
You scare me.

01:22:16.156 --> 01:22:19.489
And finally, Noodle.

01:22:19.489 --> 01:22:21.964
Biggest pile o’ the lot.

01:22:21.964 --> 01:22:24.197
But this isn’t
to pay your bill.

01:22:24.197 --> 01:22:26.804
This is to keep you here.

01:22:26.804 --> 01:22:28.102
What do you mean?

01:22:28.102 --> 01:22:30.269
My friend, Mr. Slugworth,

01:22:30.269 --> 01:22:32.876
doesn’t think
nasty little urchins like you

01:22:32.876 --> 01:22:34.273
should be out on the streets,

01:22:34.273 --> 01:22:35.846
lowering the tone.

01:22:35.846 --> 01:22:37.342
So, he gave me this money

01:22:37.342 --> 01:22:41.214
to keep you down
in the Wash House for good.

01:22:41.214 --> 01:22:44.151
And I’m only
too happy to oblige.

01:22:44.151 --> 01:22:45.383
- I hate you!
-  Hey!

01:22:45.383 --> 01:22:46.857
- Hey, hey, hey.

01:22:46.857 --> 01:22:48.518
Look at her go,
Lord Bleachowitz.

01:22:48.518 --> 01:22:50.223
- Lord Bleachowitz?

01:22:50.223 --> 01:22:53.028
You don’t still think
he’s a lord, do you?

01:22:53.028 --> 01:22:53.765
What?

01:22:53.765 --> 01:22:55.866
We made it up,
you stupid old hag.

01:22:55.866 --> 01:22:57.230
She’s...
she’s lying.

01:22:57.230 --> 01:22:59.969
Right, that’s it,
you horrible little brat.

01:22:59.969 --> 01:23:02.906
You’re goin’ in the coop,
my girl.

01:23:02.906 --> 01:23:05.909
And you!
Take them dungarees off,

01:23:05.909 --> 01:23:09.143
you... you peasant.

01:23:09.143 --> 01:23:11.112
But Puffy-wuffy.

01:23:11.112 --> 01:23:13.048
I wuv you.

01:23:39.338 --> 01:23:40.372
Hello, Noodle.

01:23:40.372 --> 01:23:44.442
Willy.
I thought you’d gone.

01:23:44.508 --> 01:23:45.212
I did.

01:23:45.212 --> 01:23:46.543
Slugworth promised you
a better life,

01:23:46.543 --> 01:23:49.546
but he didn’t exactly
keep his side of the bargain.

01:23:49.546 --> 01:23:51.218
So I came back. We all did.

01:23:51.218 --> 01:23:52.483
Hey, Noodle.
How do?

01:23:52.483 --> 01:23:54.188
Hey.
Surprise!

01:23:54.188 --> 01:23:56.256
He wants me
locked up forever.

01:23:56.256 --> 01:23:57.895
Yeah, well, that figures.

01:23:57.895 --> 01:23:59.930
Why? What’s he got against me?

01:23:59.930 --> 01:24:01.294
I don’t know, Noodle.
Not for sure.

01:24:01.294 --> 01:24:04.231
All I know for certain
is that you won’t be safe
until Slugworth

01:24:04.231 --> 01:24:07.102
- is behind bars.

01:24:07.102 --> 01:24:10.303
And how exactly
is that supposed to happen?

01:24:10.303 --> 01:24:12.074
Abacus.
You said the Cartel keep

01:24:12.074 --> 01:24:13.845
a record
of all their dirty deeds.

01:24:13.845 --> 01:24:15.011
In the green ledger, yes.

01:24:15.011 --> 01:24:16.375
So if we can
get hold o’ that,

01:24:16.375 --> 01:24:18.080
we can prove that
they poisoned our chocolate.

01:24:18.080 --> 01:24:19.851
Scrubitt and Bleacher
would go to jail,

01:24:19.851 --> 01:24:20.885
and we’ll all be free.

01:24:20.885 --> 01:24:22.612
Uh, yes, but may I remind you,

01:24:22.612 --> 01:24:24.988
they keep that ledger
in a vault.

01:24:24.988 --> 01:24:26.484
Guarded by a corrupt cleric.

01:24:26.484 --> 01:24:28.519
And 500 chocoholic monks.

01:24:28.519 --> 01:24:31.027
-  Mm-hmm.
- That’s all true.

01:24:31.027 --> 01:24:33.590
But I went for a long,
cold swim this morning.

01:24:33.590 --> 01:24:35.229
Cold water is very good
for the brain.

01:24:35.229 --> 01:24:36.967
Stimulates
the neural pathways.

01:24:36.967 --> 01:24:39.464
And after just four miles,
it came to me.

01:24:39.464 --> 01:24:41.169
How an ingenious orphan,

01:24:41.169 --> 01:24:42.269
an accountant, a plumber,

01:24:42.269 --> 01:24:44.073
a telephone exchange operator,

01:24:44.073 --> 01:24:46.075
and a man
who can speak underwater,

01:24:46.075 --> 01:24:47.142
could combine those talents,

01:24:47.142 --> 01:24:48.605
and pull off
the heist of the century.

01:24:48.605 --> 01:24:51.410
But even if we do get
our hands on that ledger,

01:24:51.410 --> 01:24:54.919
the Cartel will simply bribe
their way out of trouble.

01:24:54.919 --> 01:24:56.888
It’s what they do.

01:24:56.888 --> 01:24:58.615
The greedy
beat the needy, Willy.

01:24:58.615 --> 01:25:00.958
It’s just the way
of the world.

01:25:00.958 --> 01:25:02.058
You’re right, Noodle.

01:25:02.058 --> 01:25:03.994
I guess that’s why
there’s one other thing to do.

01:25:03.994 --> 01:25:07.657
- What’s that?
-  Change the world.

01:25:10.396 --> 01:25:11.529
Whoa!

01:25:12.937 --> 01:25:14.136
Where do we start?

01:25:26.082 --> 01:25:27.380
’Scuse me, sir.

01:25:27.380 --> 01:25:30.449
Could you spare
a piece of chocolate
for a starvin’ orphan?

01:25:30.449 --> 01:25:34.959
I’m sorry, my child.
I don’t have any on me.

01:25:34.959 --> 01:25:36.994
Oh.

01:25:37.423 --> 01:25:40.393
Then have some acacia mints.

01:25:41.097 --> 01:25:42.494
Yes!

01:25:43.935 --> 01:25:47.103
"To Basil Bond,
employee of the week."

01:25:47.103 --> 01:25:48.599
Oh, that’s lovely...

01:26:00.050 --> 01:26:02.019
Everything all right
back there?

01:26:02.019 --> 01:26:05.319
Everything’s fine.
Isn’t it, Abigail?

01:26:06.485 --> 01:26:08.157
Tell her she might
want to duck.

01:26:08.157 --> 01:26:10.489
Tell her she might
wanna what?

01:26:10.489 --> 01:26:12.227
Duck!

01:26:15.065 --> 01:26:16.330
Good morning, brethren.

01:26:16.330 --> 01:26:17.661
Good morning, Father.

01:26:17.661 --> 01:26:19.168
Now, as you all know,

01:26:19.168 --> 01:26:22.402
it’s Baron von
Schmeichelhammer’s
funeral today.

01:26:22.402 --> 01:26:25.438
And his widow is...

01:26:25.438 --> 01:26:28.111
a bit of a pious type.
-  Ugh!

01:26:28.111 --> 01:26:29.640
So, I don’t want
to see anyone

01:26:29.640 --> 01:26:32.214
eating chocolate
during the service.

01:26:32.214 --> 01:26:34.051
Yes, Father.

01:26:34.051 --> 01:26:35.151
We all know that one day,

01:26:35.151 --> 01:26:37.186
we shall be judged
for our sins,

01:26:37.186 --> 01:26:40.684
but it’s not going
to be today.

01:26:40.684 --> 01:26:43.324
Amen.

01:26:56.238 --> 01:26:58.273
There, there.

01:26:58.273 --> 01:26:59.406
Nice giraffe.

01:26:59.406 --> 01:27:02.772
- Run! Everybody out!
-  ♪ Giraffe ♪

01:27:02.772 --> 01:27:04.279
-  Run!
-  The beast!

01:27:04.279 --> 01:27:06.380
Save yourselves!
-  ♪ Giraffe ♪

01:27:06.380 --> 01:27:08.217
-  Get out!
-  ♪ It’s a giraffe ♪

01:27:08.217 --> 01:27:10.219
Judgement has come!
♪ Giraffe’s a giraffe ♪

01:27:10.219 --> 01:27:11.253
Run off! Quickly!

01:27:11.253 --> 01:27:13.255
- In a most unexpected form.
-  ♪ Got a giraffe ♪

01:27:13.255 --> 01:27:15.191
♪You’re having a laugh ♪
- Run away!

01:27:15.191 --> 01:27:16.753
♪ I know it’s a giraffe,
Giraffe, giraffe ♪

01:27:16.753 --> 01:27:18.590
What have I done
to deserve this?

01:27:18.590 --> 01:27:20.031
You know what you’ve done,
Julius.

01:27:20.031 --> 01:27:22.495
You’ve sold your soul
for 30 pieces of chocolate.

01:27:26.235 --> 01:27:28.402
Hello, operator.
How may I direct your call?

01:27:28.402 --> 01:27:31.108
I need the Zoo.
It’s an emergency.

01:27:31.108 --> 01:27:35.211
Putting you through
to the Escaped
Animal Department now.

01:27:37.147 --> 01:27:38.181
Hello, Zoo.

01:27:41.415 --> 01:27:43.516
Quiet down, you animals.

01:27:43.516 --> 01:27:44.583
You too, octopus.

01:27:44.583 --> 01:27:47.223
There’s a giraffe.
- What? Oh, yeah, I think

01:27:47.223 --> 01:27:48.719
we did lose a giraffe.

01:27:48.719 --> 01:27:50.325
Well, could you come
and get it?

01:27:50.325 --> 01:27:53.823
Okay, jeez.
I’ll send the guys around.

01:28:05.406 --> 01:28:07.672
Oh, forgive me!

01:28:08.211 --> 01:28:09.278
I’m a sinner!

01:28:09.278 --> 01:28:14.415
A weak and wicked chocoholic!

01:28:22.786 --> 01:28:23.820
Good morning, everyone.

01:28:23.820 --> 01:28:26.790
Welcome
to St. Benedict’s.

01:28:26.790 --> 01:28:30.464
Baroness,
I’m so sorry for your loss.

01:28:30.464 --> 01:28:35.667
We’re just having a few
technical difficulties, um,

01:28:35.667 --> 01:28:36.602
so you might want to pop

01:28:36.602 --> 01:28:39.143
the late baron down
for a minute.

01:28:40.672 --> 01:28:41.475
Ah, the cavalry.

01:28:41.475 --> 01:28:45.347
Are you the cleric
who called about a giraffe?

01:28:50.715 --> 01:28:52.783
All clear.

01:29:17.709 --> 01:29:19.909
Huh. "Thanks
for all your hard work."

01:29:19.909 --> 01:29:23.847
"Father Julius
and the Chocolate Cartel."

01:29:23.847 --> 01:29:26.157
Oh, that’s nice.

01:29:26.487 --> 01:29:27.158
Mmm.

01:29:27.158 --> 01:29:28.753
Here we are, Father.

01:29:28.753 --> 01:29:30.293
- One giraffe.

01:29:30.293 --> 01:29:32.559
Marvelous.
Thank you, thank you.

01:29:32.559 --> 01:29:33.824
Stand back, please.
Stand back.

01:29:33.824 --> 01:29:38.466
♪ Have I got
A sweet tooth? Pow! I do ♪

01:29:41.667 --> 01:29:42.602
Wow.

01:29:42.602 --> 01:29:44.373
♪ Have I got a sweet tooth...♪

01:29:44.373 --> 01:29:45.737
She can really move.

01:29:45.737 --> 01:29:47.838
I could’ve
been happy, but I threw
a pearl away.

01:29:47.838 --> 01:29:49.939
I’ll give him a call.
No, I can’t.

01:29:49.939 --> 01:29:52.678
I will give him a call
actually.

01:29:58.453 --> 01:29:59.289
Hello?

01:29:59.289 --> 01:30:01.621
Basil? It’s Gwennie.

01:30:01.621 --> 01:30:02.424
You were right.

01:30:02.424 --> 01:30:03.524
What are the chances?

01:30:03.524 --> 01:30:07.561
Those days in chemistry class
were the happiest of my life.

01:30:27.746 --> 01:30:29.319
Cool.

01:30:36.326 --> 01:30:37.393
Sorry about this, sir.

01:30:37.393 --> 01:30:38.724
The seafood truck
spilled its load.

01:30:38.724 --> 01:30:40.825
There’s so many blasted
flamingos about these days.

01:30:40.825 --> 01:30:42.794
Well,
hurry it along now, will you?

01:30:42.794 --> 01:30:45.302
The town square
was closed this morning

01:30:45.302 --> 01:30:48.239
after a bizarre incident
at the city cathedral.

01:30:48.239 --> 01:30:51.803
Delaying the funeral
of noted philanthropist,

01:30:51.803 --> 01:30:53.805
Baron von Schmeichelhammer.

01:30:53.805 --> 01:30:55.807
In nomine Patris,

01:30:55.807 --> 01:31:00.317
et Filii, et Spiritus Sancti.

01:31:00.383 --> 01:31:01.681
Amen.

01:31:05.586 --> 01:31:08.589
Sorry, I’d best get that.

01:31:09.557 --> 01:31:11.526
- Hello, pulpit?
-  Father.

01:31:11.526 --> 01:31:12.659
Everything all right there?

01:31:12.659 --> 01:31:14.661
Oh, yes, Mr. Slugworth.

01:31:14.661 --> 01:31:16.531
All tickety-boo.

01:31:16.531 --> 01:31:17.466
At least, it is now.

01:31:17.466 --> 01:31:19.028
- What do you mean by that?

01:31:19.028 --> 01:31:20.733
Oh, we had a giraffe
in here earlier.

01:31:20.733 --> 01:31:22.867
Had to clear the whole place
for about 20 minutes,

01:31:22.867 --> 01:31:25.672
but everything’s
back to normal.

01:31:27.575 --> 01:31:28.279
Hello?

01:31:28.279 --> 01:31:30.941
Damn the flamingos,
Donovan! Floor it!

01:31:30.941 --> 01:31:32.415
Yes, sir!

01:31:35.451 --> 01:31:36.881
Idiot!

01:31:40.423 --> 01:31:42.359
Anything?
- Nothing.

01:31:42.359 --> 01:31:43.294
Well, keep looking.

01:31:43.294 --> 01:31:44.427
It’s not in here, Willy.

01:31:44.427 --> 01:31:45.791
But Abacus said
that it was here.

01:31:45.791 --> 01:31:48.332
Abacus has been
in the Wash House
for the past four years.

01:31:48.332 --> 01:31:49.861
Maybe all the scrubbing
has gone to his head.

01:31:49.861 --> 01:31:54.503
’Cause all that’s down here
is just a bunch
of stupid old chocolate.

01:32:09.452 --> 01:32:11.322
Willy, look!

01:32:18.659 --> 01:32:19.957
We did it, Noodle.

01:32:19.957 --> 01:32:22.399
- We got ’em.

01:32:23.367 --> 01:32:25.864
Naughty, naughty,
Mr. Wonka.

01:32:25.864 --> 01:32:29.406
You’ve caused us
quite a bit of trouble.

01:32:29.406 --> 01:32:30.836
You and your urchin.

01:32:30.836 --> 01:32:32.871
Yeah, but she’s not
just an urchin,

01:32:32.871 --> 01:32:34.477
is she, Mr. Slugworth?

01:32:35.907 --> 01:32:37.909
You’re family.

01:32:37.975 --> 01:32:38.844
What?

01:32:38.844 --> 01:32:41.649
What are you talking about,
Willy?

01:32:42.485 --> 01:32:44.454
You know that ring, Noodle?

01:32:44.454 --> 01:32:46.016
The one your parents gave you?

01:32:46.016 --> 01:32:48.689
Mr. Slugworth has one
just like it.

01:32:48.689 --> 01:32:50.988
Don’t you, Mr. Slugworth?

01:32:50.988 --> 01:32:53.496
As a matter of fact, I do.

01:32:53.496 --> 01:32:58.732
That belonged to my brother.
Zebedee.

01:32:58.732 --> 01:32:59.766
Was he my father?

01:32:59.766 --> 01:33:02.406
A hopeless romantic
is what he was.

01:33:02.406 --> 01:33:05.002
Fell in love with
a common little bookworm,

01:33:05.002 --> 01:33:06.905
died before
they could marry.

01:33:06.905 --> 01:33:11.943
Leaving me sole heir
to the family fortune.

01:33:12.416 --> 01:33:14.682
Or so I thought.

01:33:14.682 --> 01:33:16.013
But nine months later,

01:33:16.013 --> 01:33:17.949
your mother turned up
on my doorstep,

01:33:17.949 --> 01:33:22.921
begging me to get a doctor
for her sick little newborn.

01:33:23.020 --> 01:33:24.857
I said I would help.

01:33:24.857 --> 01:33:27.057
But you didn’t.
Did you?

01:33:27.057 --> 01:33:28.058
Oh, no.

01:33:28.058 --> 01:33:30.929
Instead, you put me
down a laundry chute.

01:33:30.929 --> 01:33:32.700
Bye-bye, baby.

01:33:32.700 --> 01:33:34.999
Mrs. Scrubitt found me.

01:33:34.999 --> 01:33:35.967
She saw the ring.

01:33:35.967 --> 01:33:39.773
Thought it was an "N,"
and called me Noodle.

01:33:39.938 --> 01:33:40.873
But it wasn’t.

01:33:40.873 --> 01:33:43.106
It was "Z." For Zebedee.

01:33:43.106 --> 01:33:44.107
Well, quite.

01:33:44.107 --> 01:33:46.978
When your mother returned,
I told her you had died.
-  Oh, no!

01:33:46.978 --> 01:33:48.716
She was
heartbroken, of course.

01:33:48.716 --> 01:33:50.520
But, uh, I gave her
a handful of sovereigns

01:33:50.520 --> 01:33:53.985
and had her escorted
from my property.

01:33:55.426 --> 01:33:57.593
What was her name?

01:33:57.692 --> 01:33:58.660
Eh?

01:33:58.660 --> 01:34:01.663
My mom. What was her name?

01:34:02.433 --> 01:34:03.665
Ooh.

01:34:03.665 --> 01:34:05.667
Let me see. Um...

01:34:05.832 --> 01:34:08.538
No, I don’t think
I could remember that.

01:34:08.538 --> 01:34:12.168
Sorry.
But you have to understand,

01:34:12.168 --> 01:34:13.609
she was very poor.

01:34:13.609 --> 01:34:16.007
- Sorry, Felix.

01:34:16.007 --> 01:34:17.910
Her name was Dorothy.

01:34:17.910 --> 01:34:21.012
Dorothy Smith.
It says so right here.

01:34:21.111 --> 01:34:22.178
Dorothy?

01:34:22.178 --> 01:34:23.685
Well, what do you know?

01:34:23.685 --> 01:34:26.688
I guess you did teach me
to read after all.

01:34:27.458 --> 01:34:29.185
Well,
this is all very touching,

01:34:29.185 --> 01:34:30.824
but back to business.

01:34:30.824 --> 01:34:31.990
We’ll take that, thank you.

01:34:31.990 --> 01:34:35.796
How much chocolate
do you have at your factory,
Mr. Fickelgruber?

01:34:35.796 --> 01:34:37.897
Oh, about 80,000 gallons.

01:34:37.897 --> 01:34:40.064
- Prodnose?

01:34:40.064 --> 01:34:40.999
Seventy-five?

01:34:40.999 --> 01:34:43.474
And I’ve got 150.

01:34:43.606 --> 01:34:45.476
That should be enough.

01:34:45.476 --> 01:34:46.939
For what?

01:34:47.038 --> 01:34:50.646
Death by chocolate.

01:35:08.158 --> 01:35:10.061
On you go.

01:35:28.079 --> 01:35:29.850
Uh, gentlemen.

01:35:30.279 --> 01:35:31.588
Considering the situation,

01:35:31.588 --> 01:35:34.822
I wondered if you’d do
a good deed on my behalf.

01:35:34.822 --> 01:35:35.790
A what?

01:35:35.790 --> 01:35:36.626
"A good deed."

01:35:36.626 --> 01:35:39.024
It’s a sort of pointless act
of selflessness...

01:35:39.024 --> 01:35:41.532
Yes, of course, Mr. Wonka.

01:35:41.532 --> 01:35:42.962
What would you like us to do?

01:35:42.962 --> 01:35:46.603
I was wondering if you could
give this to someone.

01:35:46.801 --> 01:35:48.836
Only if you happen to see him.

01:35:48.836 --> 01:35:49.672
And who is it?

01:35:49.672 --> 01:35:52.202
A little orange man.
- Eh?

01:35:52.202 --> 01:35:53.841
A little orange man.

01:35:53.841 --> 01:35:54.776
About eight inches high,

01:35:54.776 --> 01:35:56.206
with orange skin
and bright green hair.

01:35:56.206 --> 01:35:59.748
I owe him a jar of chocolates,
you see. And, well,

01:35:59.748 --> 01:36:03.015
I think these might be
the best I ever made.

01:36:03.015 --> 01:36:03.950
Well, in that case,

01:36:03.950 --> 01:36:07.118
I’ll make sure
he gets them personally.

01:36:11.221 --> 01:36:13.597
Farewell, Mr. Wonka.

01:36:14.565 --> 01:36:15.929
Urchin.

01:36:26.874 --> 01:36:30.075
-  Willy...

01:36:54.803 --> 01:36:56.299
What are we gonna do, Willy?

01:36:56.299 --> 01:37:00.336
I don’t know, Noodle.
I’ll think of something.

01:37:06.375 --> 01:37:08.685
Best chocolate
he ever made, eh?

01:37:10.984 --> 01:37:12.920
Whoo-hoo.
- Oh!

01:37:14.218 --> 01:37:15.120
I got it!

01:37:15.120 --> 01:37:17.056
What is it?
Did you think of something?

01:37:17.056 --> 01:37:17.991
Yes, I did.

01:37:17.991 --> 01:37:19.630
If we’re gonna drown
in chocolate, Noodle,

01:37:19.630 --> 01:37:22.094
and let’s face it, we’re gonna
drown in chocolate,

01:37:22.094 --> 01:37:23.392
then it’s gonna
be Wonka chocolate.

01:37:23.392 --> 01:37:26.835
We’re not gonna drown, Willy.
Look, there’s a light.

01:37:26.835 --> 01:37:29.101
We’ll let the chocolate
lift us up,

01:37:29.101 --> 01:37:30.300
we’ll bang on the glass,

01:37:30.300 --> 01:37:32.907
and pray somebody hears us.

01:37:32.907 --> 01:37:35.173
That’s a much better idea.

01:37:37.208 --> 01:37:38.044
Ah, gentlemen.

01:37:38.044 --> 01:37:40.277
It was a bit of a close shave
this morning,

01:37:40.277 --> 01:37:41.817
and I was wondering if perhaps

01:37:41.817 --> 01:37:45.689
we could rethink
our arrangement. Or...

01:37:47.020 --> 01:37:51.189
Or... just leave things
as they are.

01:37:51.189 --> 01:37:53.059
Father.

01:37:53.158 --> 01:37:55.292
Well, Wonka might be as nutty
as a fruitcake,

01:37:55.292 --> 01:37:56.964
but he sure knew
how to make chocolate.

01:37:56.964 --> 01:37:58.361
Mmm.
- But do you think

01:37:58.361 --> 01:38:01.034
we should have saved some
for the Little Orange Man?

01:38:01.034 --> 01:38:02.134
Tell me you’re joking.

01:38:02.134 --> 01:38:05.335
Uh, yes. Yes, I am.
Sorry, why am I?

01:38:05.335 --> 01:38:07.073
Because
there’s no such thing

01:38:07.073 --> 01:38:10.406
as a little orange man,
ya nincompoop.

01:38:12.683 --> 01:38:14.685
Help!
Help!

01:38:14.685 --> 01:38:16.181
Somebody help, please!

01:38:16.181 --> 01:38:17.952
Please help!
- Help!

01:38:17.952 --> 01:38:20.823
Look. Look,
somebody’s coming. Look.

01:38:20.823 --> 01:38:23.155
Willy, we’re saved!

01:38:35.266 --> 01:38:38.808
I’m sorry, Noodle.
- Don’t be.

01:38:38.940 --> 01:38:41.173
You found my family.

01:38:41.173 --> 01:38:43.978
A mom who loved me.

01:38:43.978 --> 01:38:46.783
That’s all I ever wanted.

01:38:48.048 --> 01:38:49.951
Deep breath now.

01:39:03.195 --> 01:39:06.770
Mmm! Exquisite.

01:39:06.770 --> 01:39:09.465
You mustn’t let yourself
get so worked up.

01:39:09.465 --> 01:39:11.434
It’s just a bit of chocolate.

01:39:11.434 --> 01:39:13.403
-  Correction.

01:39:13.403 --> 01:39:17.748
It was actually my chocolate.

01:39:23.380 --> 01:39:27.252
You have made
a very grave error, gentlemen.

01:39:27.252 --> 01:39:29.485
You steal from
an Oompa Loompa,

01:39:29.485 --> 01:39:30.794
we take back

01:39:30.794 --> 01:39:32.521
a thousandfold.

01:39:39.869 --> 01:39:41.970
What’s going on, Willy?

01:39:42.069 --> 01:39:44.137
It’s draining, Noodle.

01:39:44.137 --> 01:39:46.007
We’ve been saved!

01:39:46.007 --> 01:39:49.043
- By who?
- I don’t know.

01:39:49.109 --> 01:39:51.782
By the Little Orange Man!

01:39:51.782 --> 01:39:52.508
- Look.
- Wh...

01:39:52.508 --> 01:39:54.279
The Little Orange Man!

01:39:54.279 --> 01:39:57.084
Thank you,
Little Orange Man! Thank you!

01:40:20.206 --> 01:40:23.110
Gentlemen.
Thank goodness you’re okay.

01:40:23.110 --> 01:40:25.376
I came as fast as I could.

01:40:33.384 --> 01:40:35.122
Whew! Car shrunk.

01:40:35.122 --> 01:40:36.189
I’m sure it did.

01:40:36.189 --> 01:40:38.257
And you’ve nothing
to worry about, Chief.

01:40:38.257 --> 01:40:39.192
All under control.

01:40:39.192 --> 01:40:40.589
A couple of thieves broke in,
but I’m afraid

01:40:40.589 --> 01:40:44.098
they met with a little...
accident.

01:40:44.098 --> 01:40:47.002
In which they died.

01:40:47.937 --> 01:40:49.466
That’s actually
rather good, Gerald.

01:40:49.466 --> 01:40:51.105
I wouldn’t be
so sure about that.

01:40:51.105 --> 01:40:53.976
Officer, would you kindly
take a look at this?

01:40:53.976 --> 01:40:54.471
Wonka!

01:40:54.471 --> 01:40:56.209
It details
every single illegal payment

01:40:56.209 --> 01:40:58.112
these men have ever made.

01:40:58.112 --> 01:40:59.014
Thousands of them.

01:40:59.014 --> 01:41:01.544
Affable, don’t listen
to her. She’s lyin’.

01:41:01.544 --> 01:41:03.887
Well, of course she is.

01:41:03.887 --> 01:41:05.350
She’s not, sir.

01:41:05.350 --> 01:41:07.517
She’s absolutely right.

01:41:07.583 --> 01:41:09.321
It’s incredible.

01:41:09.486 --> 01:41:10.553
Oh. Well.

01:41:10.553 --> 01:41:12.357
Then that sounds like a case

01:41:12.357 --> 01:41:13.589
for the Chief of Police.

01:41:13.589 --> 01:41:16.900
So you give it to me, Affable,
I’ll, uh...
I’ll take it off your hands.

01:41:16.900 --> 01:41:18.297
You know,
save you the paperwork.

01:41:18.297 --> 01:41:20.233
I can’t do that,
I’m afraid, sir.

01:41:20.233 --> 01:41:21.201
Why’s that?

01:41:21.201 --> 01:41:24.006
Because your name
is written down here.

01:41:24.006 --> 01:41:24.501
Huh?

01:41:24.501 --> 01:41:26.008
- A lot.
- Gentlemen...

01:41:26.008 --> 01:41:27.878
-  You’re under arrest.
-  Run.

01:41:27.878 --> 01:41:29.242
We puttin’
handcuffs on, here?

01:41:29.242 --> 01:41:30.474
- That’s okay, Noodle.

01:41:30.474 --> 01:41:32.146
Give it one second.

01:41:34.181 --> 01:41:36.150
What’s happening?

01:41:36.150 --> 01:41:37.085
Why are we airborne?

01:41:37.085 --> 01:41:38.581
You didn’t eat
any of those chocolates,

01:41:38.581 --> 01:41:40.550
did you, Mr. Slugworth?
- Why?

01:41:40.550 --> 01:41:42.057
Because
they’re Hoverchocs.

01:41:42.057 --> 01:41:44.290
Delayed action,
but extra strong.

01:41:44.290 --> 01:41:46.226
You think you’re
very clever, don’t you, Wonka?

01:41:46.226 --> 01:41:50.164
Well, there’s a billion
sovereigns of chocolate
beneath our feet.

01:41:50.164 --> 01:41:51.231
We’ll get the best lawyers,

01:41:51.231 --> 01:41:54.201
bribe the judge,
rig the jury if we have to.

01:41:54.201 --> 01:41:56.236
We’ll be fine.

01:41:56.236 --> 01:41:58.909
I wish I’d thought of that.

01:42:01.571 --> 01:42:03.276
Hey, Noodle!

01:42:21.129 --> 01:42:22.064
What is that?

01:42:22.064 --> 01:42:23.428
It’s our chocolate!

01:42:23.428 --> 01:42:25.430
All our chocolate!

01:42:25.430 --> 01:42:26.365
We’re ruined!

01:42:26.365 --> 01:42:27.971
Hey, don’t worry, gentlemen.

01:42:27.971 --> 01:42:30.468
You’ll come down eventually.

01:42:30.468 --> 01:42:33.570
Probably. I think.

01:42:33.570 --> 01:42:35.605
But until then,

01:42:35.704 --> 01:42:38.179
ladies and gentlemen,

01:42:38.179 --> 01:42:41.952
Willy Wonka and friends...

01:42:41.952 --> 01:42:45.252
...invite you
to enjoy our chocolate.

01:42:45.252 --> 01:42:48.717
Yay! Magic Wonka!

01:42:51.621 --> 01:42:53.161
Gwennie?

01:42:53.161 --> 01:42:55.427
Basil!

01:42:55.625 --> 01:42:56.967
What did I say, Abacus,

01:42:56.967 --> 01:42:59.398
I told you
we could fix it all.

01:43:16.745 --> 01:43:18.516
Your cup.

01:43:18.681 --> 01:43:19.550
Thank you.

01:43:19.550 --> 01:43:21.057
- There you are.
-  There you go.

01:43:21.057 --> 01:43:22.322
Careful, not too much.

01:43:22.322 --> 01:43:23.686
Okay.

01:45:00.849 --> 01:45:04.655
Mmm.
- Oh, thank you.

01:45:04.655 --> 01:45:05.755
Thank you.

01:45:05.755 --> 01:45:08.296
Mmm.
Thank you.

01:45:08.296 --> 01:45:10.826
Mmm.
-  Oh.

01:45:19.538 --> 01:45:21.177
Huh.

01:45:23.773 --> 01:45:28.217
So...
how does it feel, Willy?

01:45:28.283 --> 01:45:30.714
Is it as good as you remember?

01:45:31.517 --> 01:45:33.321
Every little bit.

01:45:36.456 --> 01:45:38.854
I wish it could last forever.

01:45:44.596 --> 01:45:46.598
I guess it’s time.

01:45:48.138 --> 01:45:48.765
Time for what?

01:45:48.765 --> 01:45:53.209
Do you know
